Because of `@Reference` supports the customized behavior for Dubbo Service, for example:

```java
@Reference
private UserService userService;

@Reference(protocol="dubbo")
private UserService userService;
```

If the above two fields will be enhanced as the Spring Beans, the problem is how to identify them.

dubbo 2.7.1 add an ipv4 check to avoid local site address：
```java
public boolean isSiteLocalAddress() {
        // refer to RFC 1918
        // 10/8 prefix
        // 172.16/12 prefix
        // 192.168/16 prefix
        int address = holder().getAddress();
        return (((address >>> 24) & 0xFF) == 10)
            || ((((address >>> 24) & 0xFF) == 172)
                && (((address >>> 16) & 0xF0) == 16))
            || ((((address >>> 24) & 0xFF) == 192)
                && (((address >>> 16) & 0xFF) == 168));
    }
```
